    <div class="project-overview">
        <h2 class="section-title">Project Overview</h2>
        <div class="overview-text">
            "More Together" emerged during a time when physical distance threatened to divide communities worldwide. The campaign positioned Facebook as the platform that makes meaningful connections possible, emphasizing that we're stronger when we come together around shared interests, causes, and experiences.
            <br><br>
            The platform encompassed multiple touchpoints including the 2021 Super Bowl campaign, community-building initiatives, and product features that facilitated group formation and engagement. We focused on authentic stories of how Facebook Groups, Events, and messaging helped people maintain relationships and build new ones during challenging times. The campaign celebrated ordinary people doing extraordinary things when they unite around common purpose.
            <br><br>
            The work spanned from intimate community stories to mass-market moments like the Super Bowl, consistently reinforcing that Facebook's greatest strength lies in bringing people together. Post-campaign metrics showed increased group creation, event attendance, and overall community engagement across the platform.
        </div>
    </div>

